An award-winning wood sculptor will turn tree trunks into life-size statues of The Beatles on Liverpool’s waterfront this summer. Waterloo-born Simon O'Rourke will head to the city’s Pier Head Village to take on the ambitious task of creating the four legendary band members. The ‘Fab Four’ will be carved out over four ... Rather than attempting to tell the whole story of the world’s most famous group, Ron Howard’s highly anticipated Fab Four documentary instead focuses on the history of the band through their touring years interspersed with remastered live footage - many of which never seen before. Liverpool will play host to the world premiere of Ron Howard’s upcoming documentary ‘The Beatles: Eight Days a Week - The Touring Years’. The Beatles Story has teamed up with auction house Julien’s Auctions to appraise fan memorabilia at an event next month.
